description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: This is my personal internal experience. I think it‚Äôs so different for everyone else and maybe if you‚Äôre Neuro Typical looking in at this it might seem unreasonable or ‚ÄúOver reaction‚Äù but it‚Äôs just how my brain works.  I was inspired by @commaficionado‚Äôs thread.

name: Ashley Storrie
description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: It‚Äôs like you feel betrayed by your own cognitive processes and at the same time wholly justified in your reaction, and why isn‚Äôt everyone else who‚Äôs train was cancelled sobbing?

name: Ashley Storrie
description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: And reasonably, I know that I can just go to a hotel or a friends, I can just spend another night‚Ä¶ BUT I HAVE NOT PREPARED MY BRAIN FOR THAT and change feels so cataclysmic in that moment.

name: Ashley Storrie
description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: And that brain soup just explodes out as uncontrollable sobbing and the more I try to control the worse it gets. And I know people are staring now and the one thing I want to do is squeeze myself against a wall (Where I feel comforted) but I can‚Äôt.

name: Ashley Storrie
description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: One part of my brain is catastrophising, running through the ‚ÄòWHAT IFS‚Äô. Everything around me gets louder and brighter and hotter and scarier. People look at me funny. Another part of my brain is trying to rationalise, but it‚Äôs being hampered by everything else

name: Ashley Storrie
description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: So once I can thumb down no more, and the train company has shrugged and said ‚Äúnothing can be done‚Äù and I‚Äôve explained 15 times to dad what‚Äôs happening I am at an impasse. And I go full meltdown.

name: Ashley Storrie
description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: I was diagnosed late and other than ‚ÄúThumbing Everything Down‚Äù I don‚Äôt have a lot of effective coping techniques. Usually expressing exactly what is happening and then trying to describe my feelings (which is usually difficult to understand, like ‚ÄúMy Brain feels pingy‚Äù) helps.

name: Ashley Storrie
description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: Euston makes me very anxious. It‚Äôs loud, bustling, there‚Äôs too many smells and the lighting is hell. It‚Äôs hot and I‚Äôm already at my base line level of anxiety and there‚Äôs no convenient place to self soothe. I tried sitting in a toilet once and the cleaner yelled at me.

name: Ashley Storrie
description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: A good example of ‚ÄúMelt Down‚Äù for me is a train cancellation. I need to get home from London, I‚Äôve told my brain I only have to spend 2 nights in London. I‚Äôve planned for 2 nights, prepared for 2 nights

name: Ashley Storrie
description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: I‚Äôm Hypersensitive on most fronts so for me it‚Äôs too much. And that‚Äôs sort of my base level existence. It‚Äôs why I‚Äôm most happy, alone, in my room, surrounded by my things that I like.

tweet: Our government to step up on a local and national level to do more. We need to also accept that sometimes talking about Mental Health and Mental Illness isn't nice, or kind. We need forums for family & children of those who are struggling to vent safely #MentalHealthAwarenessWeek

name: Ashley Storrie
description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: We also need to look past the acceptable faces of mental illness. You can't claim to be a mental health ally or advocate in one breath and condemn the homeless or addicted with the other, in the Venn Diagram of our society there's a lot of cross over! #MentalHealthAwarenessWeek

name: Ashley Storrie
description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: I need to work at it. They say it's like a broken leg, but you can't fix a broken leg by coming on twitter and saying "I have a broken leg". You need to reset the break, take pain killers, wear a bootie, get crutches and then rehab the injury. #MentalHealthAwarenessWeek

name: Ashley Storrie
description: Comedian, Radio host, Neuro-Funky, Actually Autistic Actor & writer. Progress not Perfection contact: Corrie McGuire Management corrie@cmmanagement.co.uk
tweet: It's the start of Mental Health awareness week, in the past month I've realised that "raising awareness" and "talking about it" aren't enough. It's great that the barriers of stigma are being crushed, but it's simply not enough #MentalHealthAwarenessWeek
